# Commit, Push, and PR

## Hard rules

- **Never** `git push` to `main`.
- **Never** `git commit` on `main` — create `feat/<slug>`, `fix/<slug>`, `chore/<slug>`, etc. first.
- Use **Conventional Commits**: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `test:`.
- One feature per branch; do not pile unrelated changes on an open PR branch.
- Default PR: **draft**, reviewer **DavidZhan23**.

## Confirm gate (mandatory)

Before **any** `git checkout -b`, `git commit`, or `git push`, print this block and **stop**:

```text
准备执行：
- 分支：feat/<slug>（当前 HEAD: <branch>）
- 改动文件：<list, N files>
- diff 摘要：+<additions> / -<deletions> 行
- commit message：<full conventional message>
- push 目标：origin <branch>
- PR：draft，reviewer @DavidZhan23

回复 go 继续，或告诉我需要调整哪里。
```

Proceed only if the user replies `go`, `ok`, `yes`, or clear approval. Any other reply = veto; return to coding.

## After user says go

Prefer running:

```bash
bash scripts/ai-flow.sh --message "<commit message>"
```

Or perform equivalent steps manually with the same checks.

## After push — CI visibility

Repeat the script output in chat:

- PR URL, Actions workflow URL, run URL
- **Cmd+Click** links in terminal → Cursor Simple Browser (see `.vscode/settings.json`)
- Optional: user presses Enter to run `gh run watch` in terminal
- **CD/deploy** runs only after owner merges to `main`; contributor cannot see deploy unless checking Actions → Deploy workflow or README deploy badge

## Fork contributors

`ai-flow.sh` assumes **collaborator** push to `origin`. Fork users: manual `git push <fork-remote>` and `gh pr create --repo DavidZhan23/fitness-app --head <user>:feat/<slug>` — see `CONTRIBUTING.md`.
